changed%2C%20your%20browser%20will%20fire%20a%26nbsp%3B%3Cstrong%3E%3Ccode%3Edownloading%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26nbsp%3Bevent%20and%20start%20re-downloading%20every%20single%20resource%20listed%20in%20the%20cache%20manifest.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EWhile%20it%26rsquo%3Bs%20downloading%2C%20your%20browser%20will%20periodically%20fire%26nbsp%3B%3Cstrong%3E%3Ccode%3Eprogress%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26nbsp%3Bevents%2C%20which%20contain%20information%20on%20how%20many%20files%20have%20been%20downloaded%20already%20and%20how%20many%20files%20are%20still%20queued%20to%20be%20downloaded.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EAfter%20all%20resources%20listed%20in%20the%20cache%20manifest%20have%20been%20re-downloaded%20successfully%2C%20the%20browser%20fires%20one%20final%20event%2C%26nbsp%3B%3Cstrong%3E%3Ccode%3Eupdateready%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20This%20is%20your%20signal%20that%20the%20new%20version%20of%20your%20offline%20web%20application%20is%20fully%20cached%20and%20ready%20to%20be%20used%20offline.%26nbsp%3B%3Cem%3EThe%20new%20version%20is%20not%20yet%20in%20use.%3C%2Fem%3E%26nbsp%3BTo%20%26ldquo%3Bhot-swap%26rdquo%3B%20to%20the%20new%20version%20without%20forcing%20the%20user%20to%20reload%20the%20page%2C%20you%20can%20manually%20call%20the%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3Ewindow.applicationCache.swapCache()%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Bfunction.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3C%2Ful%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3C%2Fol%3E%0A%3Cp%3EIf%2C%20at%20any%20point%20in%20this%20process%2C%20something%20goes%20horribly%20wrong%2C%20your%20browser%20will%20fire%20an%26nbsp%3B%3Cstrong%3E%3Ccode%3Eerror%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26nbsp%3Bevent%20and%20stop.%20Here%20is%20a%20hopelessly%20abbreviated%20list%20of%20things%20that%20could%20go%20wrong%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cul%3E%0A%3Cli%3EThe%20cache%20manifest%20returned%20an%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Berror%20404%20(Page%20Not%20Found)%20or%20410%20(Permanently%20Gone).%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EThe%20cache%20manifest%20was%20found%20and%20hadn%26rsquo%3Bt%20changed%2C%20but%20the%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTML%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bpage%20that%20pointed%20to%20the%20manifest%20failed%20to%20download%20properly.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EThe%20cache%20manifest%20changed%20while%20the%20update%20was%20being%20run.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EThe%20cache%20manifest%20was%20found%20and%20had%20changed%2C%20but%20the%20browser%20failed%20to%20download%20one%20of%20the%20resources%20listed%20in%20the%20cache%20manifest.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3C%2Ful%3E%0A%3Ch2%20id%3D%22debugging%22%3ETHE%20FINE%20ART%20OF%20DEBUGGING%2C%20A.K.A.%20%26ldquo%3BKILL%20ME!%20KILL%20ME%20NOW!%26rdquo%3B%3C%2Fh2%3E%0A%3Cp%3EI%20want%20to%20call%20out%20two%20important%20points%20here.%20The%20first%20is%20something%20you%20just%20read%2C%20but%20I%20bet%20it%20didn%26rsquo%3Bt%20really%20sink%20in%2C%20so%20here%20it%20is%20again%3A%20if%20even%20a%20single%20resource%20listed%20in%20your%20cache%20manifest%20file%20fails%20to%20download%20properly%2C%20the%20entire%20process%20of%20caching%20your%20offline%20web%20application%20will%20fail.%20Your%20browser%20will%20fire%20the%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3Eerror%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Bevent%2C%20but%20there%20is%20no%20indication%20of%20what%20the%20actual%20problem%20was.%20This%20can%20make%20debugging%20offline%20web%20applications%20even%20more%20frustrating%20than%20usual.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20important%20point%20is%20something%20that%20is%20not%2C%20technically%20speaking%2C%20an%20error%2C%20but%20it%20will%20look%20like%20a%20serious%20browser%20bug%20until%20you%20realize%20what%26rsquo%3Bs%20going%20on.%20It%20has%20to%20do%20with%20exactly%20how%20your%20browser%20checks%20whether%20a%20cache%20manifest%20file%20has%20changed.%20This%20is%20a%20three-phase%20process.%20This%20is%20boring%20but%20important%2C%20so%20pay%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Col%3E%0A%3Cli%3EVia%20normal%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bsemantics%2C%20your%20browser%20will%20check%20whether%20the%20cache%20manifest%20has%20expired.%20Just%20like%20any%20other%20file%20being%20served%20over%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%2C%20your%20web%20server%20will%20typically%20include%20meta-information%20about%20the%20file%20in%20the%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bresponse%20headers.%20Some%20of%20these%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bheaders%20(%3Ccode%3EExpires%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Band%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3ECache-Control%3C%2Fcode%3E)%20tell%20your%20browser%20how%20it%20is%20allowed%20to%20cache%20the%20file%20without%20ever%20asking%20the%20server%20whether%20it%20has%20changed.%20This%20kind%20of%20caching%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20offline%20web%20applications.%20It%20happens%20for%20pretty%20much%20every%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTML%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bpage%2C%20stylesheet%2C%20script%2C%20image%2C%20or%20other%20resource%20on%20the%20web.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EIf%20the%20cache%20manifest%20has%20expired%20(according%20to%20its%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bheaders)%2C%20then%20your%20browser%20will%20ask%20the%20server%20whether%20there%20is%20a%20new%20version%2C%20and%20if%20so%2C%20the%20browser%20will%20download%20it.%20To%20do%20this%2C%20your%20browser%20issues%20an%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Brequest%20that%20includes%20that%20last-modified%20date%20of%20the%20cache%20manifest%2C%20which%20your%20web%20server%20included%20in%20the%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bresponse%20headers%20the%20last%20time%20your%20browser%20downloaded%20the%20manifest%20file.%20If%20the%20web%20server%20determines%20that%20the%20manifest%20file%20hasn%26rsquo%3Bt%20changed%20since%20that%20date%2C%20it%20will%20simply%20return%20a%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3E304%20(Not%20Modified)%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Bstatus.%20Again%2C%20none%20of%20this%20is%20specific%20to%20offline%20web%20applications.%20This%20happens%20for%20essentially%20every%20kind%20of%20resource%20on%20the%20web.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EIf%20the%20web%20server%20thinks%20the%20manifest%20file%20has%20changed%20since%20that%20date%2C%20it%20will%20return%20an%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3E200%20(OK)%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Bstatus%20code%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20new%20file%2C%20along%20with%20new%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3ECache-Control%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Bheaders%20and%20a%20new%20last-modified%20date%2C%20so%20that%20steps%201%20and%202%20will%20work%20properly%20the%20next%20time.%20(%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bis%20cool%3B%20web%20servers%20are%20always%20planning%20for%20the%20future.%20If%20your%20web%20server%20absolutely%20must%20send%20you%20a%20file%2C%20it%20does%20everything%20it%20can%20to%20ensure%20that%20it%20doesn%26rsquo%3Bt%20need%20to%20send%20it%20twice%20for%20no%20reason.)%20Once%20it%26rsquo%3Bs%20downloaded%20the%20new%20cache%20manifest%20file%2C%20your%20browser%20will%20check%20the%20contents%20against%20the%20copy%20it%20downloaded%20last%20time.%20If%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20cache%20manifest%20file%20are%20the%20same%20as%20they%20were%20last%20time%2C%20your%20browser%20won%26rsquo%3Bt%20re-download%20any%20of%20the%20resources%20listed%20in%20the%20manifest.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3C%2Fol%3E%0A%3Cp%3EAny%20one%20of%20these%20steps%20can%20trip%20you%20up%20while%20you%26rsquo%3Bre%20developing%20and%20testing%20your%20offline%20web%20application.%20For%20example%2C%20say%20you%20deploy%20one%20version%20of%20your%20cache%20manifest%20file%2C%20then%2010%20minutes%20later%2C%20you%20realize%20you%20need%20to%20add%20another%20resource%20to%20it.%20No%20problem%2C%20right%3F%20Just%20add%20another%20line%20and%20redeploy.%20Bzzt.%20Here%26rsquo%3Bs%20what%20will%20happen%3A%20you%20reload%20the%20page%2C%20your%20browser%20notices%20the%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3Emanifest%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Battribute%2C%20it%20fires%20the%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3Echecking%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Bevent%2C%20and%20then...%20nothing.%20Your%20browser%20stubbornly%20insists%20that%20the%20cache%20manifest%20file%20has%20not%20changed.%20Why%3F%20Because%2C%20by%20default%2C%20your%20web%20server%20is%20probably%20configured%20to%20tell%20browsers%20to%20cache%20static%20files%20for%20a%20few%20hours%20(via%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bsemantics%2C%20using%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3ECache-Control%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Bheaders).%20That%20means%20your%20browser%20will%20never%20get%20past%20step%201%20of%20that%20three-phase%20process.%20Sure%2C%20the%20web%20server%20knows%20that%20the%20file%20has%20changed%2C%20but%20your%20browser%20never%20even%20gets%20around%20to%20asking%20the%20web%20server.%20Why%3F%20Because%20the%20last%20time%20your%20browser%20downloaded%20the%20cache%20manifest%2C%20the%20web%20server%20told%20it%20to%20cache%20the%20resource%20for%20a%20few%20hours%20(via%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bsemantics%2C%20using%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3ECache-Control%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Bheaders).%20And%20now%2C%2010%20minutes%20later%2C%20that%26rsquo%3Bs%20exactly%20what%20your%20browser%20is%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20clear%2C%20this%20is%20not%20a%20bug%2C%20it%26rsquo%3Bs%20a%20feature.%20Everything%20is%20working%20exactly%20the%20way%20it%26rsquo%3Bs%20supposed%20to.%20If%20web%20servers%20didn%26rsquo%3Bt%20have%20a%20way%20to%20tell%20browsers%20(and%20intermediate%20proxies)%20to%20cache%20things%2C%20the%20web%20would%20collapse%20overnight.%20But%20that%26rsquo%3Bs%20no%20comfort%20to%20you%20after%20you%20spend%20a%20few%20hours%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20why%20your%20browser%20won%26rsquo%3Bt%20notice%20your%20updated%20cache%20manifest.%20(And%20even%20better%2C%20if%20you%20wait%20long%20enough%2C%20it%20will%20mysteriously%20starts%20working%20again!%20Because%20the%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bcache%20expired!%20Just%20like%20it%26rsquo%3Bs%20supposed%20to!%20Kill%20me!%20Kill%20me%20now!)%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3ESo%20here%26rsquo%3Bs%20one%20thing%20you%20should%20absolutely%20do%3A%20reconfigure%20your%20web%20server%20so%20that%20your%20cache%20manifest%20file%20is%20not%20cacheable%20by%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bsemantics.%20If%20you%26rsquo%3Bre%20running%20an%20Apache-based%20web%20server%2C%20these%20two%20lines%20in%20your%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3E.htaccess%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Bfile%20will%20do%20the%20trick%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cpre%3E%3Ccode%3EExpiresActive%20On%20ExpiresDefault%20%22access%22%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fpre%3E%0A%3Cp%3EThat%20will%20actually%20disable%20caching%20for%20every%20file%20in%20that%20directory%20and%20all%20subdirectories.%20That%26rsquo%3Bs%20probably%20not%20what%20you%20want%20in%20production%2C%20so%20you%20should%20either%20qualify%20this%20with%20a%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3E%26lt%3BFiles%26gt%3B%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Bdirective%20so%20it%20only%20affects%20your%20cache%20manifest%20file%2C%20or%20create%20a%20subdirectory%20that%20contains%20nothing%20but%20this%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3E.htaccess%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Bfile%20and%20your%20cache%20manifest%20file.%20As%20usual%2C%20configuration%20details%20vary%20by%20web%20server%2C%20so%20consult%20your%20server%26rsquo%3Bs%20documentation%20for%20how%20to%20control%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bcaching%20headers.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EOnce%20you%26rsquo%3Bve%20disabled%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTTP%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bcaching%20on%20the%20cache%20manifest%20file%20itself%2C%20you%26rsquo%3Bll%20still%20have%20times%20where%20you%26rsquo%3Bve%20changed%20one%20of%20the%20resources%20in%20the%20appcache%2C%20but%20it%26rsquo%3Bs%20still%20at%20the%20same%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EURL%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bon%20your%20web%20server.%20Here%2C%20step%202%20of%20the%20three-phase%20process%20will%20screw%20you.%20If%20your%20cache%20manifest%20file%20hasn%26rsquo%3Bt%20changed%2C%20the%20browser%20will%20never%20notice%20that%20one%20of%20the%20previously%20cached%20resources%20has%20changed.%20Consider%20the%20following%20example%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cpre%3E%3Ccode%3ECACHE%20MANIFEST%20%23%20rev%2042%20clock.js%20clock.css%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fpre%3E%0A%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20change%26nbsp%3B%3Ccode%3Eclock.css%3C%2Fcode%3E%26nbsp%3Band%20redeploy%20it%2C%20you%20won%26rsquo%3Bt%20see%20the%20changes%2C%20because%20the%20cache%20manifest%20file%20itself%20hasn%26rsquo%3Bt%20changed.%20Every%20time%20you%20make%20a%20change%20to%20one%20of%20the%20resources%20in%20your%20offline%20web%20application%2C%20you%26rsquo%3Bll%20need%20to%20change%20the%20cache%20manifest%20file%20itself.%20This%20can%20be%20as%20simple%20as%20changing%20a%20single%20character.%20The%20easiest%20way%20I%26rsquo%3Bve%20found%20to%20accomplish%20this%20is%20to%20include%20a%20comment%20line%20with%20a%20revision%20number.%20Change%20the%20revision%20number%20in%20the%20comment%2C%20then%20the%20web%20server%20will%20return%20the%20newly%20changed%20cache%20manifest%20file%2C%20your%20browser%20will%20notice%20that%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20file%20have%20changed%2C%20and%20it%20will%20kick%20off%20the%20process%20to%20re-download%20all%20the%20resources%20listed%20in%20the%20manifest.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cpre%3E%3Ccode%3ECACHE%20MANIFEST%20%23%20rev%2043%20clock.js%20clock.css%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fpre%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22a%22%3E%E2%9D%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Ch2%20id%3D%22halma%22%3ELET%26rsquo%3BS%20BUILD%20ONE!%3C%2Fh2%3E%0A%3Cp%3ERemember%20the%20Halma%20game%20that%20we%20introduced%20in%26nbsp%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fdiveintohtml5.org%2Fcanvas.html%23halma%22%3Ethe%20canvas%20chapter%3C%2Fa%3E%26nbsp%3Band%20later%20improved%20by%26nbsp%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fdiveintohtml5.org%2Fstorage.html%23halma%22%3Esaving%20state%20with%20persistent%20local%20storage%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Let%26rsquo%3Bs%20take%20our%20Halma%20game%20offline.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3ETo%20do%20that%2C%20we%20need%20a%20manifest%20that%20lists%20all%20the%20resources%20the%20game%20needs.%20Well%2C%20there%26rsquo%3Bs%20the%20main%26nbsp%3B%3Cabbr%3EHTML%3C%2Fabbr%3E%26nbsp%3Bpage%2C%20a%20single%